Environment: Linux, vim/nano, opsys server

How to compile the project:
  Type 'make'

How to run the project:
  ./oss [-h] [-n proc] [-s simul] [-t timelimitForChildren] [-i fractionOfSecond] [-f logfile]

Options:
-h    Print help message
-n proc    Total number of worker processes to launch (default: 5)
-s simul    Max simultaneously running workers (default: 3)
-t timelimitForChildren    Upper bound in seconds for how long a child runs (default: 5)
-i fractionOfSecond    Simulated-time interval between launching new children (default: 1.0)
-f logfile    Log file for oss output (default: oss.log)

Project Description:
This project adds message passing (System V message queues) to the P2 process simulator.
Oss launches worker children and coordinates them via a message queue in round-robin order.
Workers block on msgrcv until oss sends them a turnm then check the simulated clock and reply with 1 (still running) or 0 (terminating). The process table is now local to oss (not shared memory).
The clock is still in shared memory. oss terminates after 60 real seconds (SIGALRM) or when all workers have finished.

Outstanding issues:
None known.

Files:
- oss.c: Operating system simulator (parent process)
- worker.c: Worker process (child process)
- shared.h: Shared definitions header
- Makefile: Build configuration
- README: This file

